# ============================================
# NOTES FOR DEPLOYMENT
# ============================================
#
# COOLIFY DEPLOYMENT:
# -------------------
# 1. In Coolify, add all REACT_APP_* variables as BUILD ARGUMENTS (not runtime env vars)
# 2. React embeds these at build time, so changes require rebuild
# 3. Never use the .env file directly in production (copy values to Coolify)
#
# GITHUB ACTIONS CI/CD:
# ---------------------
# 1. Add all variables as GitHub Secrets
# 2. They will be injected during automated builds
# 3. Keep secrets separate from public variables
#
# SECURITY:
# ---------
# 1. NEVER commit .env files with real values to Git
# 2. Add .env* to .gitignore
# 3. Rotate API keys regularly (every 3-6 months)
# 4. Restrict all public API keys by domain/IP
# 5. Keep secret keys on backend only (Razorpay Secret, PayPal Secret, Stripe Secret)
#
# PUBLIC vs SECRET KEYS:
# ----------------------
# PUBLIC (safe in client-side code):
#   - Firebase API Key
#   - Agora App ID
#   - Google Maps API Key
#   - Razorpay Key ID
#   - PayPal Client ID
#   - Stripe Publishable Key
#   - OneSignal App ID
#   - Google/Facebook OAuth Client IDs
#
# SECRET (NEVER in client-side code):
#   - Firebase Service Account Key
#   - Razorpay Key Secret
#   - PayPal Secret
#   - Stripe Secret Key
#   - Agora App Certificate
#   - Database passwords
#   - JWT secrets
#
# RESTRICTIONS:
# -------------
# After obtaining API keys, restrict them in provider dashboards:
#
# Firebase:
#   - Firebase Console → Settings → Authorized domains → Add: 2sweety.app
#
# Google Maps:
#   - Google Cloud Console → Credentials → Edit API Key
#   - Application restrictions: HTTP referrers
#   - Add: https://2sweety.app/*, http://localhost:3000/*
#
# Agora:
#   - Agora Console → Enable App Certificate
#   - Implement token-based auth on backend
#
# OneSignal:
#   - Dashboard → Settings → Allowed Origins → Add: https://2sweety.app
#
# Payment Gateways:
#   - Add 2sweety.app to authorized domains in each gateway's dashboard
#
